-- Home Depot confirms data breach at U.S. and Canada stores
-- By Shailaja Sharma in Bangalore
-- Mon Sep 08, 2014 04:54PM EDT
-- None



Sept 8 (Reuters) - Home improvement retailer Home Depot <HD.N> on Monday confirmed its payment systems were breached, potentially impacting customers using payment cards at its U.S. and Canadian stores.

While the full scope of the breach was yet to be determined, there was no evidence that debit PIN numbers were compromised, Home Depot said in a statement. [ID:nPn7VtFHN] There was no evidence that the breach had impacted stores in Mexico or customers who shopped on its website, the company said. Home Depot said the investigation is focused from April onwards.